race.comment: FARNANHEIT (3) finished second, beaten 2 lengths, when resuming from a spell last start over 1100m at Stony Creek. He'll be better for that and looks more suitable venue for his racing style. TAG TIME (8) is a big watch, if for no other reason than Lane going aboard. He has a good record with Scott Cameron and TAG TIME was good enough on debut to suggest he could measure up here from the good gate. RUMBLE TOWN (6) took advantage of the good draw and led for much of the way last start before being run down late, which followed a good run here. SABERTOOTH (7) is the first-starter who could bob up after rounding out preparations with a 1000m trial win at Cranbourne.
